## üß™ Augmentation Techniques

Augmentation is applied **only on the training set** (never on test/validation) to prevent data leakage.

### ‚úÖ Noise Injection
- **Gaussian noise**: zero-mean, std = 0.01 √ó signal std  
- **White noise**: flat power spectrum  
- **Pink noise**: EEG-like, power ‚àù 1/f  
- **Brownian noise**: low-frequency dominant, simulates drift  

### ‚úÖ Time Shifting
- Circular shift along the time axis (¬±5‚Äì10 samples)  
- Helps model generalize across phase variations

